  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The 50th anniversary of John Lennon's birth was observed with a global celebration today as his peace anthem ``Imagine'' was played for an estimated 1 billion people in 130 nations.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The song was played shortly after 10 a.m. following a brief ceremony at the United Nations that featured the ex-Beatle's widow, Yoko Ono.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   ``In celebration of John's life, let's use our power of dreaming,'' Ono said.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   ``Let's dream of trees growing in abundance, birds flying in clear air, fish swimming in clear water and our children living in joy.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   ``Let's dream of men and women feeling good together and people embracing each other regardless of their creed and religion,'' she said.
